{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a transparent plastic container (gel will stick to metal or glass) onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in cold oil. Place in freezer and chill 5 minutes or until ready to use.","Place water into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>2 min 30 sec\/212°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add agar-agar by sprinkling around edge of mixing bowl avoiding the blades and cook <nobr>15 sec\/212°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add grape juice concentrate and without measuring cup cook <nobr>2 min\/212°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>, while slowly sprinkling locust gum through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl and blades with spatula, insert measuring cup and cook <nobr>15 sec\/212°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Pour grape juice mixture into a pitcher with a narrow spout. Slowly and carefully, tilt pitcher over oil in cold plastic container so that small droplets fall into the oil. Uniformly sized droplets give a better result. Let droplets rest for 3 minutes to gel.","With a large spoon or spherification spoon, carefully remove grape pearls from oil and allow to drain on paper towels. Transfer to a plastic container with lid and refrigerate until ready to use. Store in refrigerator up to five days.","Place ½ tsp grape pearls into each of six champagne flutes, pour 6 oz champagne into each glass and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["16 oz canola oil, cold","4 oz water","¾ tsp agar-agar powder","6 oz grape juice concentrate, Concord","¼ tsp locust bean gum","1 bottle champagne"]}],"id":"r416625","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-CGnHTYPX37U\/XZMvvxTVeFI\/AAAAAAAAaVs\/8w7q84Ipx9gq2VjeRJOXRij7Z-x1DQooACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_oNod5apB5x2IF0xv.png","title":"Concord Grape Pearls with Champagne (Bill Yosses)","publishedAt":"2019-03-29T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"pitcher with narrow spout or funnel pitcher, slotted or spherification spoon, paper towels, champagne flutes, transparent plastic container, plastic container with lid, refrigerator, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Recipe makes enough pearls for 30 drinks."],"basicInfo":["advanced","35m","40m","6 portions"]}